This paper is related to natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which specifically deals with NLP research. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper evaluates machine learning and deep neural network models. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as emotion recognition is a subfield of AI. The fourth likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as emotion recognition can be used in sentiment analysis and information retrieval tasks. The fifth likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper discusses the role of emotion recognition in measuring the brand value of a product.
